-- Mexico Stocks: Wal-Mart de Mexico, ICA, Cemex Shares Were Active
-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 2012-05-21T20:21:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-21/mexico-stocks-wal-mart-de-mexico-ica-cemex-shares-are-active.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Mexico City. Stock symbols are in parentheses,
and prices are as of the close of trading in Mexico City.  The  IPC index  gained 1.7 percent to 37,512.41.  Most Mexican stocks rallied, led by construction-related
companies, as  China  signaled it would support growth and German
and French officials said they will work to keep  Greece  in the
euro, buoying confidence in the global economy.  Empresas ICA SAB (ICA*)  , the country’s biggest
construction company, jumped 5.4 percent to 20.66 pesos.  Cemex SAB (CEMEXCPO)  , the largest cement maker in the
Americas, climbed 6.9 percent to 7.64 pesos.  Wal-Mart de Mexico SAB  (WALMEXV MM), Latin America’s
largest retailer, gained 4.4 percent to 37.33 pesos. It was
raised to hold from sell at Deutsche Bank AG by Reinaldo Santana, an analyst at the firm.  To contact the reporter on this story:
